     These graph templates may be used to reproduce the figures in
the book or they may be modified to display new calculated results.
The GRAPHER (c) and SURFER (c) graphics programs were configured to
create PostScript Printer *.out files for subsequent printing on a
PostScript laser printer.  The symbol sets set4.sym and set15.sym
were used.


     Four FORTRAN programs are also included:

     2.for:   generates the data for Fig. 4.2

     3.for:   generates the data for Fig. 4.3

    23.for:   generates the data for Fig. 4.23

  grid.for:   generates data points for a semicircle for use in
              Figs. 4.29 and 4.33.


     Most of the figures obtain all data points from a single run
of a program.  For example, the data graphed in Fig. 4.4 was
generated by a single run of program s1.  The graph template for
Fig. 4.4, 4.grf, reads the data file s1.dat as input.

     However, multiple runs are sometimes required to generate all
of the data points for a figure, e.g., program s6 must be run twice
to generate scattering results for both external and internal
intensities in Fig. 4.25.  In this case, the first s6.dat file must
be renamed before running the program a second time.  The graph
template 25.grf requires that the data files be named to conform to
the graph legend, i.e., in Fig. 2.25, the external intensity is set
to appear as the solid line and the internal intensity as the
dashed line.  When a figure requires multiple files as input, the
names of the files will be specified in the list below, indicating
